        <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics11-6fa0.png" height="22" width="103"/>
      </media>
    </figure>
    <para id="import-auto-id1165242955728">Hence spontaneous magnetization is high up to Curie Temperature. At Curie Temperature exchange coupling is disrupted by thermal fluctuations and material becomes paramagnetic.</para>
